[West Nile virus activity is on the rise, with a higher number of cases being reported this year (2018) with multiple outbreaks across Europe. This is largely due to the early start of the 2018 transmission season in the WHO European Region, which normally lasts from July to October. This year's season has been characterized by high temperatures and extended rainy spells, followed by dry weather. Such weather conditions have been conducive to mosquito breeding and propagation. - Mod.UBA]

